text: Cooper Island (High & Left of Center) & Long Island (RHS) Cooper Island is an island in Fiordland, in the southwest of New Zealand's South Island. It lies within Dusky Sound, east of Long Island. The island is part of Fiordland National Park and is the third-largest island in the park with no possums present. ==See also== * Desert island * List of islands ==References== Category:Uninhabited islands of New Zealand Category:Islands of Fiordland Category:Fiordland National Park
